{"questionId":"9743","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A manager wishes to check the mean&nbsp;mass of flour put into bags in his factory. He randomly&nbsp;samples 10 bags and finds the mean&nbsp;mass is 1.478 kg and the standard deviation of the&nbsp;sample is 0.0196 kg.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{s_{n - 1}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>s</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <mi>n</mi>\n        <mo>−</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n      </mrow>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> for this sample.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{s_{n - 1}} = \\sqrt {\\frac{{10}}{9}}&nbsp; \\times 0.0196 = 0.02066 \\ldots \">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>s</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <mi>n</mi>\n        <mo>−</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n      </mrow>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <msqrt>\n    <mfrac>\n      <mrow>\n        <mn>10</mn>\n      </mrow>\n      <mn>9</mn>\n    </mfrac>\n  </msqrt>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mn>0.0196</mn>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0.02066</mn>\n  <mo>…</mo>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9743","referenceCode":"SPM.1.AHL.TZ0.9a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find s n − 1 for this sample.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","AHL 4.14—Linear transformation of a single RV, E(X) and VAR(X), unbiased estimators","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","AHL 4.16—Confidence intervals"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}